The article discusses a series of executive orders issued by President Donald Trump on January 18, 2021, regarding the protection of judges, prosecutors, and law enforcement officers. The purpose of these orders is to enhance the safety of these public servants and their families, who face unique risks due to their work. The orders aim to remove obstacles preventing current and retired federal law enforcement officers from carrying concealed firearms, expand the ability of federal prosecutors to carry firearms, prioritize the protection of federal judges and prosecutors, and propose legislation to further enhance their protection. The orders also call for a review of the feasibility of minimizing the availability of personally identifiable information of these individuals and increasing penalties for violence against them and their families. The Attorney General is tasked with implementing these orders and proposing relevant regulations and legislation.